DENGUE/DHF UPDATE 2008 (21)
****************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1] Peru
[2] Brazil (Rio de Janeiro)
[3] Laos
[4] Viet Nam (Ho Chi Minh City)
[5] Hong Kong ex Maldives

******
[1] Peru
Date: Sat 24 May 2008
Source: Ministerio de Salud, Alerta Epidemiologica [in Spanish,
trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.oge.sld.pe/vigilancia/Alertas/2008/Alerta005-14052008.pdf>


During the current year [2008], starting with epidemiological week
[EW] 06 [3-9 Feb 2008] the Alto Amazonas network began to report
cases of dengue imported into the area coming from Iquitos (5 cases)
and Tarapoto (4 cases), and between EW 10 and 17 [2 Mar - 26 Apr
2008], an increase in cases began to be observed in Yurimaguas city,
coinciding with the rainy season, which is usual and persistent in
this area. In EW 18 [27 Apr - 2 May 2008], there has been a reduction
in the number of dengue cases, with a total of 98 cases of classical
dengue and one probable dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) case in
Yurimaguas. The NMRCD [USA Navy laboratory in Lima] confirmed
isolation of dengue 4 [virus] from a patient living in Yurimaguas.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[A map of the Peruvian upper Amazon showing the location of
Yurimaguas can be accessed at
<http://geology.com/world/peru-satellite-image.shtml>.
- Mod.TY]

******
[2] Brazil (Rio de Janeiro)
Date: Wed 21 May 2008
Source: Globo [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/Rio/0,,MUL489832-5606,00-CHEGA+A+O+NUMERO+DE+MORTOS+POR+DENGUE+NO+ESTADO.html>


The state Secretariat of Health this Wed 21 May 2008 reported a new
total of dengue cases. Up to the present, 155 985 dengue cases have
been reported, and the confirmed number of [dengue] deaths in Rio de
Janeiro state has reached 110.

According to the report of the Secretariat, the age group most
affected by the disease are people 15-49 years of age, which account
for 54 percent of the cases.

According to the Secretariat, 42 percent of the [dengue] deaths have
occurred in children 0-15 years of age, and 38 deaths were from DHF.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[A map of Brazil showing the location of Rio de Janeiro can be accessed at:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/brazil.jpg>.
- Mod.TY]

******
[3] Laos
Date: Fri 16 May 2008
Source: Vientiane Times [edited]
<http://www.vientianetimes.org.la/FreeContent/FreeContent_dengue.htm>


Health officials are warning the public to make sure their homes and
gardens are free of stagnant water to prevent mosquitoes from
breeding, after the mosquito-borne dengue fever virus claimed 3 lives
in [the southern provinces of] Champassak and Saravan this year [2008].

The National Centre for Laboratory and Epidemiology issued the
warning in a bid to reduce the incidence of dengue fever in the wet season.

So far this year [2008], there have been 581 cases of dengue fever,
including 3 deaths: 2 in Champassak and one in Saravan province.

Dr Phengta said the number of people falling ill with dengue fever
was increasing gradually every week. He attributed this to increasing
rainfall and higher incidence of the virus in neighboring countries.

--
Communicated by:
PRO/MBDS <promed-mbds@promedmail.org>

[A map of Laos can be accessed at:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/laos_pol_2003.jpg>.
- Mod.TY]

